<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS - Removal
        - Camshaft Bushings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26508.1.7" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Determine necessity of replacing bushings based on running clearance .</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use existing camshaft bushing kit with Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet)
                to remove all camshaft bushings. Install Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet in
                collapsed state) in camshaft bushing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650817" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0621.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft bushing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw (from camshaft bushing kit)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble pulling screw in Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet) and tighten
                backup nut until collet fits snug in camshaft bushing. To avoid nicks on bushings, be careful when
                inserting or removing threads of pulling screw.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Hold a wrench on end of pulling screw to prevent screw from turning.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650818" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0623.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Camshaft bushing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach pulling plate, thrust bearing, and drive nut on pulling screw. Tighten nut against
                thrust bearing and pulling plate. Continue to thread nut on pulling screw until camshaft bushing is free
                from crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
